    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix Authentication Failure Timer Values\n\n### Summary\nThe authentication failure timers T3418 and T3420 had incorrect default values that violated 3GPP TS 24.301 timing requirements. This caused the UE to use wrong timer durations during authentication failure handling procedures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/EMM/emmData.h`: Corrected T3418 and T3420 default timer values to match 3GPP specification\n  - T3418 (MAC authentication failure timer): changed from 20 seconds to 15 seconds\n  - T3420 (Synch authentication failure timer): changed from 15 seconds to 20 seconds\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen the UE receives an AUTHENTICATION FAILURE message:\n1. For MAC failure causes, T3418 timer is started with incorrect 20-second duration instead of 15 seconds\n2. For synchronization failure causes, T3420 timer is started with incorrect 15-second duration instead of 20 seconds\n3. This timing mismatch can cause premature or delayed authentication failure handling procedures\n\nThe issue manifests as non-compliance with 3GPP TS 24.301 section 5.4.2.7 timing requirements for authentication failure procedures.\n"
}